Class AbstractLayoutStage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.layout.AbstractLayoutStage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILayoutAlgorithm, ILayoutStage
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractLabeling, BufferedLayout, BusRouter, ChannelEdgeRouter, ComponentLayout, CompositeLayoutStage, CurveFittingLayoutStage, EdgeRouter, FixGroupLayoutStage, FixNodeLayoutStage, FixPortLocationStage, GraphLayoutLineWrapper, HandleNaNCoordinatesStage, HideGroupsStage, LayoutMultiplexer, MinimumNodeSizeStage, MultiPageLayout, NormalizeGraphElementOrderStage, OrganicPartitionGridLayoutStage, OrganicRemoveOverlapsStage, OrientationLayout, OrthogonalPatternEdgeRouter, OrthogonalSegmentDistributionStage, ParallelEdgeRouter, PartialLayout, PartitionGridLayoutStage, PartitionLayout, PolylineLayoutStage, PortCalculator, PortPlacementStage, RecursiveGroupLayout, RecursiveShuffleLayout, RemoveCollinearBendsStage, ReverseEdgesStage, SelfLoopRouter, SnapOuterPortsToNodeBorderStage, StraightLineEdgeRouter, SubgraphLayout, TopLevelGroupToSwimlaneStage, TreeReductionStage

    public abstract class AbstractLayoutStage
extends Object
implements ILayoutStage
    Abstract base class implementing ILayoutStage that handles the management of the core layout algorithm.

    Subclasses of this stage can use the provided methods, such that the management of the core layout algorithm does not need to be considered anymore.

    See Also:
    MultiStageLayout

        public abstract void applyLayout(LayoutGraph graph)
        Description copied from interface: ILayoutAlgorithm
        Main layout routine that assigns new layout information to the given graph.

        The call to this routine will only succeed if the layout algorithm can handle the input graph.

        Specified by:

        Parameters:

      • applyLayoutCore

        protected void applyLayoutCore(LayoutGraph graph)
        Invokes the layout process of the core layout algorithm.

        Overriding classes may call this method during ILayoutAlgorithm.applyLayout(LayoutGraph) to delegate arranging the graph to the core layout algorithm. They can add pre- and post-processing code before and after this call.

        Parameters:
        graph - the input graph
